3D laser scanners are segmented based on their type, range, and offering. In terms of type, they can be handheld, tripod mounted, or automated & CMM-based. Handheld scanners are portable and easy to use, making them ideal for capturing data in various environments. Tripod-mounted scanners are more stable and precise, suitable for detailed scans. Automated and CMM-based scanners are often used in industrial settings for efficient, automated scanning processes. Range segmentation includes short, medium, and long-range scanners, each suitable for different applications. Short-range scanners are used for small-scale projects with detailed requirements, while long-range scanners are preferred for large-scale projects that require high accuracy over longer distances. Lastly, scanners are offered as hardware, software, or services, providing flexibility to users based on their specific needs.

