The global 3D laser scanner market is witnessing significant growth due to the increasing demand for precise and efficient scanning solutions across various industries. Short-range scanners are preferred for detailed projects requiring high accuracy at close range, while medium-range scanners cater to a broader range of applications with moderate precision needs. Long-range scanners find extensive use in large-scale projects such as infrastructure development, urban planning, and archaeological surveys. The tripod-mounted scanners offer stability and accuracy for stationary scanning tasks, while the portability of handheld scanners allows for flexibility in data capture across different environments. Automated and CMM-based scanners provide advanced scanning capabilities, particularly in industrial applications where speed and efficiency are paramount.

